          <h3 style="font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 8px;">UPC (Universal Product Code)</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0;">A barcode used to identify products and track them in retail environments.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="glossary-term" id="up-selling" style="padding: 22px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);">
          <h3 style="font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 8px;">Up-selling</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0;">A sales technique that persuades a customer to purchase a more expensive or upgraded version of a product they are already considering, increasing the average ticket and, ultimately, business revenue. Effective upselling requires good customer data, such as purchase history and preferences.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="glossary-term" id="user-permissions" style="padding: 22px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);">
          <h3 style="font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 8px;">User Permissions</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0;">Settings within POS software that control the level of access different employees have to various features and data.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="letter-v" style="padding-top: 40px; padding-bottom: 0;">
    <div class="container">
